                                                                                               NIST SP 800-161r1                              CYBERSECURITY SUPPLY CHAIN RISK MANAGEMENT
                                                                                                                                                 PRACTICES FOR SYSTEMS AND ORGANIZATIONS


                                                                                                Term                      Definition
                                                                                                element                   See supply chain element.

                                                                                                enhanced overlay          An overlay that adds processes, controls, enhancements, and
                                                                                                                          additional implementation guidance specific to the purpose of
                                                                                                                          the overlay.
                                                                                                exposure                  Extent to which an organization and/or stakeholder is subject
                                                                                                [ISO Guide 73, adapted]   to a risk
                                                                                                external system service   A system service that is provided by an external service
