                                                                                                [NIST SP 800-53 Rev. 5]   provider and for which the organization has no direct control
                                                                                                                          over the implementation of required security and privacy
                                                                                                                          controls or the assessment of control effectiveness.
                                                                                                external system service   A provider of external system services to an organization
                                                                                                provider                  through a variety of consumer-producer relationships,
                                                                                                [NIST SP 800-53 Rev. 5]   including joint ventures, business partnerships, outsourcing
                                                                                                                          arrangements (i.e., through contracts, interagency agreements,
                                                                                                                          lines of business arrangements), licensing agreements, and/or
                                                                                                                          supply chain exchanges.
                                                                                                fit for purpose           Used informally to describe a process, configuration item, IT
                                                                                                [ITIL Service Strategy,   service, etc., that is capable of meeting its objectives or service
                                                                                                adapted]                  levels. Being fit for purpose requires suitable design,
                                                                                                                          implementation, control, and maintenance.

                                                                                                ICT/OT-related service    Any organization or individual providing services which may
                                                                                                providers                 include authorized access to an ICT or OT system

                                                                                                impact                    The effect on organizational operations, organizational assets,
                                                                                                [NIST SP 800-53 Rev. 5]   individuals, other organizations, or the Nation (including the
                                                                                                                          national security interests of the United States) of a loss of
                                                                                                                          confidentiality, integrity, or availability of information or a
                                                                                                                          system.
                                                                                                Information and           Encompasses the capture, storage, retrieval, processing,
                                                                                                Communications            display, representation, presentation, organization,
                                                                                                Technology                management, security, transfer, and interchange of data and
                                                                                                [ISO/IEC 2382, adapted]   information.
                                                                                                information system        A discrete set of information resources organized for the
                                                                                                [NIST SP 800-53 Rev. 5]   collection, processing, maintenance, use, sharing,
                                                                                                                          dissemination, or disposition of information.
                                                                                                life cycle                Evolution of a system, product, service, project, or other
                                                                                                [ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288,      human-made entity.
                                                                                                adapted]



